  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Management Executive",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Scope:</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prepare and cook a variety of dishes (stir-fry, dim sum, noodles, rice, soups, and specialty dishes) according to recipes and restaurant standards</li>\n  <li>Ensure food is cooked and presented in a timely manner while maintaining consistency in quality and portion control</li>\n  <li>Manage kitchen operations including food preparation, cooking, and plating</li>\n  <li>Maintain cleanliness and hygiene of the kitchen, cooking equipment, and workstations in compliance with food safety regulations</li>\n  <li>Monitor inventory, assist in ordering ingredients, and minimize food wastage</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with the kitchen team and communicate effectively with service staff to ensure smooth operations</li>\n  <li>Follow workplace safety procedures and handle kitchen equipment responsibly</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Proven experience as a Cook/Chef in a restaurant or hotel</li>\n  <li>Ability to work under pressure in a fast-paced environment</li>\n  <li>Good teamwork and communication skills</li>\n  <li>Flexibility to work shifts, weekends, and public holidays</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Interested candidate please email cv to geraldine@link2.com.sg OR Whatsapp 89524450</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Lee Mei Kiew Geraldine (Li Meijiao)</p>\n<p>CEI Reg: R1331173</p>\n<p>Link2 Manpower Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>MOM Reg No. 22C1131</p>",
